33
00:02:59.678 --> 00:03:05.030
the massive Steinway of
just three years later,

34
00:03:05.030 --> 00:03:10.130
1867, only three years after
the end of the American Civil War.

35
00:03:10.130 --> 00:03:11.900
The Steinway in the Yale Collection is so

36
00:03:11.900 --> 00:03:15.430
big that it requires a special
corner all to itself.

37
00:03:15.430 --> 00:03:19.490
Notice that it's far bigger
than any instrument we've seen,

38
00:03:19.490 --> 00:03:21.110
the biggest in the collection.

39
00:03:21.110 --> 00:03:25.320
We've arrived at the nine foot
long concert grand of today.

40
00:03:25.320 --> 00:03:28.764
But the year is only 1867.

41
00:03:28.764 --> 00:03:33.041
It was built, not in Vienna or
in Berlin by Germans, but

42
00:03:33.041 --> 00:03:39.570
by German immigrants coming to America,
in this case one Henrick Steinweg.

43
00:03:39.570 --> 00:03:43.480
Now, Herr Steinweg soon became Mr.

44
00:03:43.480 --> 00:03:48.850
Steinway, who setup a piano manufacturing
company in New York in the 1850s.

45
00:03:49.920 --> 00:03:55.140
