senior curator of the collection

46
00:03:55.140 --> 00:03:58.670
to introduce us to this
massive new instrument.

47
00:04:00.030 --> 00:04:01.420
So welcome to America,

48
00:04:01.420 --> 00:04:07.220
that burgeoning dynamic new country in
which technology was changing everything.

49
00:04:07.220 --> 00:04:12.520
We're going to take a look now and
a listen to beautiful large Steinway

50
00:04:12.520 --> 00:04:14.879
piano that has a signficantly different

51
00:04:15.910 --> 00:04:20.550
sound to it than the one we just heard
with the earlier Wagnerian Bechstein.

52
00:04:20.550 --> 00:04:24.210
So we've left Germany, Switzerland,
and now we are only three years later

53
00:04:25.230 --> 00:04:27.640
in the United States with
this new Steinway piano.

54
00:04:29.330 --> 00:04:33.790
>> This instrument, dating from 1867,
was made at a time when our

55
00:04:33.790 --> 00:04:39.330
country was coming of age, not only
industrially, but culturally as well.

56
00:04:39.330 --> 00:04:42.590
Examples such as this, and
instruments by Steinway's rival,

57
00:04:42.590 --> 00:04:47.220
Chickering, set the European
industry on its ears.

58
00:04:47.220 --> 00:04:51.110
They were appalled that we
had done something that so

59
00:04:51.110 --> 00:04:54.880
impressed the public and
musicians as well.

60
00:04:54.880 --> 00:04:57.963
What we see here is
a complete unitary cast iron

61
00:04:57.963 --> 00:05:02.880
frame that's absolutely rigid in its
resistance of the string tension.

62
00:05:02.880 --> 00:05:07.940
So even greater sonority is
possible with this instrument.

63
00:05:07.940 --> 00:05:14.450
It has the overstrung bass that made
history as well as the cast iron frame.

64
00:05:14.450 --> 00:05:17.080
And it gives us really the modern piano.

65
00:05:18.930 --> 00:05:23.310
>> It also, I should add,
has a very different action.

66
00:05:23.310 --> 00:05:25.340
And when we speak of the piano action,

67
00:05:25.340 --> 00:05:29.748
it's the way the keys react
when they're depressed.

68
00:05:29.748 --> 00:05:33.326
And this is a very,
very sensitive action but

69
00:05:33.326 --> 00:05:37.949
certainly not as sensitive as
some of the earlier pianos.

70
00:05:37.949 --> 00:05:40.457
>> [LAUGH]
>> Nothing is as sensitive as that first

71
00:05:40.457 --> 00:05:42.300
Beethoven piano.

