made by Nicholas and Robert,

79
00:06:42.928 --> 00:06:48.218
the massive size of the Steinway is
made possible owing to an innovation

80
00:06:48.218 --> 00:06:53.172
of an American company in Boston,
the Chickering Piano Company.

81
00:06:53.172 --> 00:07:00.920
Now Chickering introduced the uniform or
single piece cast iron frame.

82
00:07:00.920 --> 00:07:06.010
Now you can see on the left here,
the German Bechstein of 1864 with

83
00:07:07.400 --> 00:07:12.890
the pieces of iron that are attached
to other pieces of iron.

84
00:07:14.180 --> 00:07:21.330
With the Steinway, there is much more
iron surrounding the entire sound board.

85
00:07:22.570 --> 00:07:24.530
it's all one piece, single cast.

86
00:07:25.870 --> 00:07:30.710
And a second point, Robert mentioned
the over stringing of the Steinway.

87
00:07:30.710 --> 00:07:34.340
You can see with the Bechstein on
the left that the bass strings

88
00:07:34.340 --> 00:07:38.300
run out in a straight line
with the other strings.

89
00:07:38.300 --> 00:07:42.710
To the right you see that
the Steinway company decided to

90
00:07:42.710 --> 00:07:48.020
take those bass strings and
run them up and over the middle strings.

91
00:07:48.020 --> 00:07:51.920
The earlier Bechstein
did have an advantage.

92
00:07:51.920 --> 00:07:55.270
Parallel stringing did
produce a very clear sound.

93
00:07:55.270 --> 00:08:01.172
The Steinway, with its overstringing,
creates a richer, more homogenous sound.

94
00:08:01.172 --> 00:08:06.153
And after Steinway really all
grand pianos were made with this

95
00:08:06.153 --> 00:08:08.460
overstringing technique.

96
00:08:08.460 --> 00:08:12.946
But as we can see,
the overstringing is more readily apparent

97
00:08:12.946 --> 00:08:17.550
here on this overhead photo
of a modern Steinway.

98
00:08:17.550 --> 00:08:21.130
The middle strings run straight out.

99
00:08:21.130 --> 00:08:23.320
Follow the red arrow there straight out.

100
00:08:23.320 --> 00:08:29.440
While the low bass strings ride up and
over, as indicated by the blue arrow.

101
